software: After his death, Whitaker's estate sat for several years before it was placed on auction. Eventually members of the community came together to purchase the estate and donate it to the National Trust. An Irish businessman, William Pirrie, eventually purchased the mansion. Interestingly enough, Perrie was chairman of Harland & Wolfe, the company responsible for building the RMS Titanic. Pirrie's nephew was the designer of the RMS Titanic, and died in its maiden voyage.
